a time there was a land - a land of milk and honey, inhabited by happy and prosperous people. The people paid taxes, of course - their happiness had limits. But there were no taxes in Sherwood. This was Rhye's Land - the stressed-out, industrialized, post-apocalyptic hellhole that we know and love as the USA today. Taxes! Why, when has a government ever gone out of its way to make its citizens' lives worse?
